+sfwi Interval
.RS 2
Sets scheduler-forced wakeup interval. All run queues are scanned each 
\fIInterval\fR milliseconds. While there are sleeping schedulers in the system, one scheduler is woken for each non-empty run queue found. \fIInterval\fR default to \fI0\fR, meaning this feature is disabled.
.PP
\fBNOTE: \fRThis feature has been introduced as a temporary workaround for long-executing native code, and native code that does not bump reductions properly in OTP. When these bugs have been fixed, this flag will be removed.



