.RS 2
Sets default scheduler hint for port parallelism. If set to 
\fItrue\fR, the virtual machine schedules port tasks when it improves parallelism in the system. If set to \fIfalse\fR, the virtual machine tries to perform port tasks immediately, improving latency at the expense of parallelism. Default to \fIfalse\fR. The default used can be inspected in runtime by calling \fIerlang:system_info(port_parallelism)\fR. The default can be overridden on port creation by passing option \fIparallelism\fR to \fIerlang:open_port/2\fR.

