.RS 2
Sets a limit on how long the runtime system is allowed to perform flush operations while halting. Valid 
\fI<timeout>\fR values are integers in the range \fI0..2147483647\fR or the word \fIinfinity\fR. \fI<timeout>\fR is in milliseconds and is by default \fIinfinity\fR.
.PP
